# Feature comparison skill

When asked to run the weekly docs check, audit documentation coverage, find undocumented features, draft missing docs, or check what shipped vs. what's documented, follow the orchestrator instructions in `.cursor/skills/feature-comparison/SKILL.md`.

The skill coordinates multiple specialized agents. Read the SKILL.md **agent map** to pick the right agent for the task:

- **Weekly report** (most common): read `agents/report-agent.md`
- **Set up weekly schedule**: read `agents/schedule-agent.md`
- **Draft docs after approval**: read `agents/draft-agent.md` — one agent per feature, never combined
- **Ad-hoc research**: read `agents/research-agent.md`

## Key repo facts for this skill

- **Docs content:** repo root section directories (`feature-flags/`, `sdks/`, `experiments/`, etc.)
- **Navigation:** `docs.json` — `navigation.tabs[].groups[].pages` array — must be updated when adding new pages
- **GitHub repo:** `statsig-io/docs`
- **Callout syntax:** Mintlify MDX components — `<Note>`, `<Warning>`, `<Tip>`, `<Info>` — never markdown blockquotes
- **Frontmatter:** `title`, `description` (optional) — no `id`, `blueprint`, `updated_at`, `landing`, or `nav_title`
- **Internal links:** `/[section]/[slug]` — no `.mdx` extensions
- **Style gate:** run the full edit-doc skill (`.cursor/skills/edit-doc/SKILL.md` or `.claude/skills/edit-doc/SKILL.md`) on every drafted MDX file before committing

## Known channel configuration

- **Feature releases channel:** `#feature-releases` — [CONFIGURE: set the channel ID in SKILL.md before first run]
- **Report destination:** `#docs-private` — [CONFIGURE: set the channel ID in SKILL.md before first run; always use ID directly, never search by name]
